# 5. たまにはのんびり

Haruka: In the peaceful light of the ever-shining sun in the days of spring...
Airi: Got it!
Minori: What?! Already?!
Rin: Wow, Airi! You're so quick!
Minori: I didn't even know which card to reach for...
Miku: Don't worry, Minori! We just started!
Minori: Miku...! Yeah, you're right!
Minori: We can beat them if we try really hard!
Haruka: The color of the flower has already faded away while in idle thoughts...
Airi: Got it!!
Minori: How?! I thought I could get this one...!
Airi: Next, we'll be playing Fukuwarai!
Haruka: Right. Shizuku, would you like to go first?
Shizuku: Yes, sounds good!
Rin: Good luck, Shizuku!
Shizuku: Hmm, is this... An eye?
Minori: Nooo! Shizuku, that's a cheek...
Airi: Shush, Minori! Don't say anything until everything's in place...!
Miku: But it really is hard to stay quiet during this.
Shizuku: It's you guys...
Haruka: Oh, no. It's nothing. Keep going, Shizuku!
Shizuku: Okay then... What could this be...?
Shizuku: I'm guessing this is the mouth? I put an eye here, so the mouth should go... Here!
Rin: Wh-What?! There?!
Minori: Shizuku's so... Bold...!
Haruka: To be fair, she is blindfolded...
Shizuku: Finished! How did I do?
Haruka: It's straight out of a horror movie...
Minori: I-It's like a Picasso painting! I like what you did with it, Shizuku!
Shizuku: Oh, thank you so much!
Airi: Man, I don't even know where to start with this one...
Airi: Sigh... I'm spent... But that was fun!
Haruka: It was a nice change from what we usually do.
Shizuku: Hehe. We were so into it, we completely forgot about the camera sometimes.
Minori: Yeah, it was great!
Minori: Wait... NOOO! I forgot we were recording too!
Shizuku: Welcome to the club, I guess?
Minori: Wh-What do we do?! We had it all planned out so neatly, and I went off script right there...
Airi: Don't beat yourself up over something like that.
Haruka: Exactly. Why don't we see how the video turned out?
Minori: O-Okay...
Minori: Oh...!
Rin: This video's great!
Miku: Yeah! Everyone's having so much fun playing those games!
Shizuku: Oh, but this is a bit embarrassing... I put a cheek where an eye should be and the mouth where the nose should be during Fukuwarai...
Rin: We were all really on edge when you did that...!
Minori: I was really worried because it didn't all go as we planned...
Airi: But it actually turned out pretty well in the end, right?
Airi: It's like this with live shows too. You can plan all you want, but things never really follow the script while the cameras are rolling.
Airi: Plus, it's usually better when you're just yourself and go with the flow.
Minori: Oh, I see...!
Haruka: Spoken like a true professional, Airi.
Airi: Weren't you thinking the same, Haruka? I mean, I'm sure that's why you let things go off script the way they did.
Haruka: Well, that was part of it but...
Shizuku: But...?
Haruka: Everyone was having so much fun, I wanted to preserve that vibe.
Miku: Hehe! You all look so happy and enthusiastic in the video!
Rin: Yeah, you can't help but smile while watching it!
Haruka: Thank you, Miku and Rin!
Shizuku: Hehe, I wish I hadn't made such silly mistakes in front of the camera, but if you liked the video, then I'm happy with it too.
Minori: Right. And it was a good learning experience!
Haruka: Well, that was a good test run. How about we take what we learned from it and work out what we'll do for the real thing?
Miku: Haruka, before you go, would you like to stay here a bit longer and have some fun?
Haruka: Huh?
Rin: We're celebrating the New Year, so it would be great if we could spend more time chatting!
Miku: I want to try Fukuwarai too!
Airi: Hmm. We have been crazy busy lately, so maybe we should just take it easy for a change...
Haruka: Right. We can draw up our plans whenever so...
Shizuku: Let's celebrate the New Year together!
Minori & Rin: Yeah!
